<item>
            <title>[HBASE-10708] Memory leak in HBaseTestingUtility</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-10708</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I can no longer run the Phoenix unit tests on my Mac (OS X 10.8.5) using Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 1.6.0_65-b14-462-11M4609). It works fine on HBase 0.94.14 and earlier. However, with later version, it gets slower and slower and eventually dies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To repro, get the latest from the 3.0 branch of Phoenix and follow the maven build instructions here: &lt;a href=&quot;http://phoenix.incubator.apache.org/building.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://phoenix.incubator.apache.org/building.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It&apos;ll complete on 0.94.14 (in about 1 hr), but fail on later version.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Mac&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
